<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="113.[151,639,1230,1729]" lastBlockId="113.[685,1173,194,826]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,280,1575,1596]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from the other species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sharp Desig. Park and Carlton" authorityYear="2013" box="[473,546,1602,1623]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Sagola" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="misella">
<emphasis box="[473,546,1602,1623]" italics="true" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">misella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
speciesgroup by the following combination of characters: larger body, length 
<quantity box="[355,480,1655,1677]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.7">2.7–2.8 mm</quantity>
; male antennomeres 4–10 enlarged; eye larger, approximately one-half length of temple; shape of antennomeres and genitalia unique to species; only known from 
<collectingRegion box="[741,838,221,242]" country="New Zealand" name="Southland" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Southland</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="113" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="113.[685,1173,194,826]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[709,913,247,268]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Description of Male.</emphasis>
Length 
<quantity box="[997,1112,247,269]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.7" pageId="113" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="2.75" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.7">2.7–2.8 mm</quantity>
. Body brown, antennae, legs, maxillary palpi, and elytra paler (
<figureCitation box="[750,837,300,321]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="103.[175,208,1340,1359]" captionTargetBox="[155,1159,183,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-228@103.[151,1171,183,1317]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="Fig. 58. Habitus of Sagola species in the misella species-group, dorsal views. a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. southlandensis, l) S. huvali, m) S. tennysonensis. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907892/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 58k</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[857,919,300,321]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Head:</emphasis>
Round, as long as wide, widest across eyes (
<figureCitation box="[897,991,327,348]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="103.[175,208,1340,1359]" captionTargetBox="[155,1159,183,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-228@103.[151,1171,183,1317]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="Fig. 58. Habitus of Sagola species in the misella species-group, dorsal views. a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. southlandensis, l) S. huvali, m) S. tennysonensis. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907892/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 58k</figureCitation>
). Antennomere 1 approximately 1.5 times longer than wide, 2–10 subquadrate, 4–10 enlarged, 6–11 with tubercles. Frontal rostrum rectangular, lobes continuous. Frontal sulcus reaching midpoint of eye. Posterior frontal fovea elongate. Eye prominent, approximately one-half length of temple. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1090,1172,486,507]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Thorax:</emphasis>
Prosternum as long as wide, widest at midpoint. Elytra rectangular (
<figureCitation box="[883,974,539,560]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="103.[175,208,1340,1359]" captionTargetBox="[155,1159,183,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-228@103.[151,1171,183,1317]" captionTargetPageId="103" captionText="Fig. 58. Habitus of Sagola species in the misella species-group, dorsal views. a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. southlandensis, l) S. huvali, m) S. tennysonensis. Scale bars = 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907892/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 58k</figureCitation>
). Meso- and metathorax trapezoidal, longer than wide. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1064,1171,566,587]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Abdomen:</emphasis>
Male tergite IV without pair of patches of microtrichia. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[759,864,619,640]" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Aedeagus:</emphasis>
Median lobe of genitalia triangular, curved as S-shaped vertically (
<figureCitation box="[1075,1161,646,667]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="104.[197,230,972,991]" captionTargetBox="[183,1189,190,937]" captionTargetId="figure-477@104.[173,1193,183,948]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="Fig. 59. Sagola species in the misella species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. otagoensis, apical lobe, lateral view, l) S. southlandensis, m) S. huvali, n) S. tennysonensis. S. misella: o) Dorsal surface of head, p) Prosternum, ventral view, q) Meso- and metaventrites, ventral view, r) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907896/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 59l</figureCitation>
). Phallobase of median lobe symmetrical and rounded (
<figureCitation box="[779,860,699,720]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="104.[197,230,972,991]" captionTargetBox="[183,1189,190,937]" captionTargetId="figure-477@104.[173,1193,183,948]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="Fig. 59. Sagola species in the misella species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. otagoensis, apical lobe, lateral view, l) S. southlandensis, m) S. huvali, n) S. tennysonensis. S. misella: o) Dorsal surface of head, p) Prosternum, ventral view, q) Meso- and metaventrites, ventral view, r) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907896/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 59l</figureCitation>
). Parameres asymmetrical, right longer than left, with setae apically (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1133,725,746]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="104.[197,230,972,991]" captionTargetBox="[183,1189,190,937]" captionTargetId="figure-477@104.[173,1193,183,948]" captionTargetPageId="104" captionText="Fig. 59. Sagola species in the misella species-group. Aedeagi, dorsal views: a) S. misella, b) S. bituberata, c) S. prisca, d) S. murchisonensis, e) S. fiordlandensis, f) S. hunterensis, g) S. humpridgensis, h) S. clunieae, i) S. turretensis, j) S. otagoensis, k) S. otagoensis, apical lobe, lateral view, l) S. southlandensis, m) S. huvali, n) S. tennysonensis. S. misella: o) Dorsal surface of head, p) Prosternum, ventral view, q) Meso- and metaventrites, ventral view, r) Abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars = 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4907896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4907896/files/figure.png" pageId="113" pageNumber="114">Fig. 59l</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
